hiPathWirelessDot11ExtnsMIB.name: hiPathWirelessDot11ExtnsMIB

revisions.description: Updated contact information. Corrected syntax error in dot11ExtSmtDcsMode.
Added antenna selection. Added more radio attributes to dot11ExtSmtTable. Added radio stats (dot11ExtRadioStatsTable).
- Additional radio attributes were added to dot11ExtSmtTable. - dot11gBasicG was obsoleted. - dot11bBasicB was obsoleted.
Added antenna diversity for radios. accocIfIndex syntax and description were modified.

hiPathWirelessDot11ExtnsMIB.contactinfo: Behrouz Sultan Chantry Networks, Inc. 1900 Minnesota Court, Suite 125 Mississauga ON, L5N 3C9 Email: behrouz.sultan@siemens.com Phone 1-905-288-3537 Fax 1-905-567-0099
hiPathWirelessDot11ExtnsMIB.description: This module provides extension objects to the ieee80211 MIB.

dot11ExtBSSIDTable.name: dot11ExtBSSIDTable
dot11ExtBSSIDTable.description: The dot11ExtBSSIDTable contains a list of the BSS (Basic Service Set) Identifiers supported by each radio, and associates an SSID with with each BSS.

dot11ExtBSSIDEntry.name: dot11ExtBSSIDEntry
dot11ExtBSSIDEntry.description: An entry in the BSSID table.

dot11ExtBSSIndex.name: dot11ExtBSSIndex
dot11ExtBSSIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, that identifies each Basic Service Set Identifier (BSSID) supported by a radio.

dot11ExtBSSID.name: dot11ExtBSSID
dot11ExtBSSID.description: The Basic Service Set Identifier (BSSID) uniquely identifies a wireless network adapter. In the case of the AP2620, a radio can support up to 8 distinct BSSIDs.

dot11ExtSSIDID.name: dot11ExtSSIDID
dot11ExtSSIDID.description: SSIDID is a High Path Wireless internal numeric identifier for the SSID. This number is meaningless external to the product.

dot11ExtSSID.name: dot11ExtSSID
dot11ExtSSID.description: The Service Set Identifier (SSID) is the network name identifying the wireless network to which this adapter belongs.

dot11ExtBSSIDWEPKeyIndex.name: dot11ExtBSSIDWEPKeyIndex
dot11ExtBSSIDWEPKeyIndex.description: Specifies the WEP default key associated with this BSS from the ieee802dot11 dot11WEPDefaultKeysTable.

dot11ExtSSIDSuppress.name: dot11ExtSSIDSuppress
dot11ExtSSIDSuppress.description: When True, the radio will not broadcast the SSID associated with this BSSID in the beacons.

dot11ExtPriorityTrafficHandling.name: dot11ExtPriorityTrafficHandling
dot11ExtPriorityTrafficHandling.description: When True, priority traffic handling is enabled for this BSSID.

dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingsTable.name: dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingsTable
dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingsTable.description: The dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingsTable supports the ability to configure a separate WEP key for each BSS/Station pairing. The WEPKeyMappingValues in this table are logically WRITE-ONLY. Any attempt to read these values will return null or 0.

dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingIndex.name: dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingIndex
dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the WEP Key Mappings Table.

dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingAddress.name: dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingAddress
dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingAddress.description: The MAC address of the STA for which the values from this key mapping entry are to be used.

dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingWEPOn.name: dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingWEPOn
dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingWEPOn.description: Boolean as to whether WEP is to be used when communicating with the dot11WEPKeyMappingAddress STA.

dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingStatus.name: dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingStatus
dot11ExtWEPKeyMappingStatus.description: The status column used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the columnar objects in the WEP key mapping Table.

dot11CapabilitiesTable.name: dot11CapabilitiesTable
dot11CapabilitiesTable.description: The dot11CapabilitiesTable contains the 802.11 protocols that each radio in the accessPoint are capable of supporting.

dot11Capabilities.name: dot11Capabilities
dot11Capabilities.description: Describes the capabilities of a radio, for example the protocol supported.

dot11bConfigTable.name: dot11bConfigTable
dot11bConfigTable.description: The table contains configuration elements specific to the 802.11b protocol.

dot11bConfigEntry.name: dot11bConfigEntry
dot11bConfigEntry.description: The dot11bConfigTable contains configuration elements specific to the 802.11b protocol. If an attempt to read the elements is made for a radio which does not support 802.11b, null or 0 will be returned.

dot11bEnabled.name: dot11bEnabled
dot11bEnabled.description: When true, 802.1b protocol support is active on this radio.

dot11BasicB.name: dot11BasicB
dot11BasicB.description: Specifies the basic rate set for a 11b or 11b+g radio. When set to basic11b, the radio uses all four 11b rates (1, 2, 5.5 and 11 Mbps) as basic rates. When when set to basic11 the radio uses only the two 11 rates (1 and 2 Mbps) as basic rates.

dot11gConfigTable.name: dot11gConfigTable
dot11gConfigTable.description: The dot11gConfigTable contains configuration elements specific to the 802.11g protocol. If an attempt to read the elements is made for a radio which does not support 802.11g, null or 0 will be returned.

dot11gEnabled.name: dot11gEnabled
dot11gEnabled.description: When true, 802.1g protocol support is active on this radio.

dot11gProtectionMode.name: dot11gProtectionMode
dot11gProtectionMode.description: Configures whether and when to use Protection Mode for the 802.11g transmissions. Protection Mode helps reduce collisions with legacy 802.11b stations at the expense of additional overhead. None specifies that no protection is to be used. Auto specifies that radio will enable protection mode when it detects an 802.11b station. Always specifies that protection mode is always enabled.

dot11gProtectionType.name: dot11gProtectionType
dot11gProtectionType.description: Determines whether 802.11g Protection Mode uses a RTS-CTS sequence or a CTS-only protection mechanism when Protection Mode is enabled.

dot11gProtectionRate.name: dot11gProtectionRate
dot11gProtectionRate.description: Specifies the rate to be used by RTS or CTS in protection mode.

dot11gBasicG.name: dot11gBasicG
dot11gBasicG.description: Specifies the set of basic rates in 11-g-only mode. Default allows all possible basic rates (1, 2, 5.5, 11, 6, 12 and 24 Mbps). Basic11 specifies only 11 rates (1 nad 2 Mbps) as basic. Basic11b specifies all four 11b rates (1, 2, 5.5 and 11 Mbps) as basic. OFDM specifies only OFDM rates (6, 12 and 24 Mbps) as basic.

dot11gProtectionModeSelected.name: dot11gProtectionModeSelected
dot11gProtectionModeSelected.description: Protection mode selected by Access Point. Values are: off(0) = protection mode is set to off by Access Point. on(1) = protection mode is set to on by Access Point. notAvailable(2) = protection mode status is not available, either due to Access Point's version or stats have not yet been collected by Controller.

dot11ExtSmtEntry.name: dot11ExtSmtEntry
dot11ExtSmtEntry.description: An entry in the Extended settings table dot11ExtSmtTable.

smtShortPreambleInvoked.name: smtShortPreambleInvoked
smtShortPreambleInvoked.description: Specifies the type of preamble used in an 11b/g radio: always short, always long or automatically selected.

dot11ExtSmtCurrentChannel.name: dot11ExtSmtCurrentChannel
dot11ExtSmtCurrentChannel.description: Specfies the current radio channel. Value of zero means 'auto' selection.

dot11ExtSmtMinBasicRate.name: dot11ExtSmtMinBasicRate
dot11ExtSmtMinBasicRate.description: Specifies the minimum basic rate which is also the minimum operational rate.

dot11ExtSmtCurChanSelectedByAP.name: dot11ExtSmtCurChanSelectedByAP
dot11ExtSmtCurChanSelectedByAP.description: Current channel selected by Access Point.

dot11ExtSmtRFDomain.name: dot11ExtSmtRFDomain
dot11ExtSmtRFDomain.description: Identifies a radio as belonging to an RF Domain. This is used to provide dynamic radio management when all SSIDs are suppressed.

dot11ExtSmtCurrentTxPowerLevel.name: dot11ExtSmtCurrentTxPowerLevel
dot11ExtSmtCurrentTxPowerLevel.description: Current transmission power level of the radio.

dot11ExtSmtMaxTxPower.name: dot11ExtSmtMaxTxPower
dot11ExtSmtMaxTxPower.description: Maximum transmission power level of the radio.

dot11ExtSmtMinTxPower.name: dot11ExtSmtMinTxPower
dot11ExtSmtMinTxPower.description: Minimum transmission power level of the radio.

dot11ExtSmtBGretries.name: dot11ExtSmtBGretries
dot11ExtSmtBGretries.description: Number of retries for Background traffics.

dot11ExtSmtBEretries.name: dot11ExtSmtBEretries
dot11ExtSmtBEretries.description: Number of retries for Best Efforts traffics.

dot11ExtSmtVIretries.name: dot11ExtSmtVIretries
dot11ExtSmtVIretries.description: Number of retries for Video traffics.

dot11ExtSmtVOretries.name: dot11ExtSmtVOretries
dot11ExtSmtVOretries.description: Number of retries for Voice traffics.

dot11ExtSmtTVOretries.name: dot11ExtSmtTVOretries
dot11ExtSmtTVOretries.description: Number of retries for Turbo Voice traffics.

dot11ExtSmtDcsNoiseThreshold.name: dot11ExtSmtDcsNoiseThreshold
dot11ExtSmtDcsNoiseThreshold.description: DCS Nose Threshould. It determines at which interface level the AP will decide to look for a ne operating channel. The unit is dBm. It is valid only when DCS operation mode is set to monitor or active

dot11ExtSmtDcsChlOccThreshold.name: dot11ExtSmtDcsChlOccThreshold
dot11ExtSmtDcsChlOccThreshold.description: DCS Channel Occupancy Threshold. It determines at which channel utilization the AP decides to look for a new operating channel. The unit is % percentage. It is valid only when DCS operation mode is set to monitor or active

dot11ExtSmtDcsUpdatePeriod.name: dot11ExtSmtDcsUpdatePeriod
dot11ExtSmtDcsUpdatePeriod.description: DCS Update Period. It determines the period during which the AP averages the DCS Noise Threshold & DCS channel Occupancy Threshold measurements. The unit is minutes. The range is 1-15. The 0 means DCS is disabled. It is valid only when DCS operation mode is set to monitor or active

dot11ExtSmtDcsChannelSelection.name: dot11ExtSmtDcsChannelSelection
dot11ExtSmtDcsChannelSelection.description: DCS Channel Plan Selection.It is Bitmask of: 1 = all chls (only A), 2 = 3 chls (only BG), 4 = 4 chls (only BG), 8 = auto (only BG), 16 = custom

dot11ExtSmtDcsChannelList.name: dot11ExtSmtDcsChannelList
dot11ExtSmtDcsChannelList.description: DCS Channel Plan List.It is custom channel plan. It is valid only when DCS Channel Plan Selection is set to custom

dot11ExtVlanSmtTable.name: dot11ExtVlanSmtTable
dot11ExtVlanSmtTable.description: This table contains configuration about bridging mode for the radio.

vlanBridgeMode.name: vlanBridgeMode
vlanBridgeMode.description: When true, bridging mode is enabled on this radio.

vlanTag.name: vlanTag
vlanTag.description: Integer specifying the VLAN tag. If untagged, returns -1.

dot11DiversityTable.name: dot11DiversityTable
dot11DiversityTable.description: List of configuration elements specific to diversity support.

dot11AntennaSelection.name: dot11AntennaSelection
dot11AntennaSelection.description: Antenna Selection for transmission and reception.

dot11nConfigTable.name: dot11nConfigTable
dot11nConfigTable.description: The dot11nConfigTable contains configuration elements specific to the 802.11n protocol. If an attempt to read the elements is made for a radio which does not support 802.11n, null or 0 will be returned.

dot11nEnabled.name: dot11nEnabled
dot11nEnabled.description: When true, 802.1n protocol support is active on this radio.

dot11nAggrMsduSubFrames.name: dot11nAggrMsduSubFrames
dot11nAggrMsduSubFrames.description: 802.11n protocol Aggregate MPDU Max Number of Sub-frames.

dot1XConfigTable.name: dot1XConfigTable
dot1XConfigTable.description: Conceptual table for 802.1X settings required for wireless security.

dot1XDynamicRekeyingInterval.name: dot1XDynamicRekeyingInterval
dot1XDynamicRekeyingInterval.description: This object defines the time period, in seconds, after which the key value must be updated.

dot1XWPA1Enabled.name: dot1XWPA1Enabled
dot1XWPA1Enabled.description: Enables WPA.1 (Wi-Fi Protected Access) on this BSSID

dot1XWPAPassphrase.name: dot1XWPAPassphrase
dot1XWPAPassphrase.description: Specifies the WPA passphrase for the BSSID. This element is logically write only. Any attempt to read this element will result in null or 0.

dot1XWPACipherType.name: dot1XWPACipherType
dot1XWPACipherType.description: Defines the encryption algoritms allowed with WPA: only TKIP if tkipOnly or both AES and TKIP if auto. This value has meaning if WPA.1 is enabled.

dot1XWPA2Enabled.name: dot1XWPA2Enabled
dot1XWPA2Enabled.description: When true, WPA v.2 support is enabled.

dot1XWPA2CipherType.name: dot1XWPA2CipherType
dot1XWPA2CipherType.description: Defines the encryption algoritms allowed with WPA2: only AES if aesOnly or both AES and TKIP if auto. This value has meaning if WPA.2 is enabled.

dot1XConfigKeyManagement.name: dot1XConfigKeyManagement
dot1XConfigKeyManagement.description: Key caching method in use. This field has meaning when dot1XEnabled is true and WPAv2 is enabled.

assocGroupEntry.name: assocGroupEntry
assocGroupEntry.description: Entry in the STA statistics table.

assocAddress.name: assocAddress
assocAddress.description: MAC address associated with the client.

assocIfIndex.name: assocIfIndex
assocIfIndex.description: Index of the radio mode with which the client is associated. Values are: 11A =1, 11G =2 and 11B =3.

assocReceivedRSSI.name: assocReceivedRSSI
assocReceivedRSSI.description: Received signal strength for the packets received from this client.

assocTransmittedRSSI.name: assocTransmittedRSSI
assocTransmittedRSSI.description: Received signal strength averaged for the ACK packets received in response to transmitted packets for this client.

assocReceivedRate.name: assocReceivedRate
assocReceivedRate.description: PHY rate for the packets received from this client.

assocTransmittedRate.name: assocTransmittedRate
assocTransmittedRate.description: PHY rate used to transmit packets for this client.

assocReceiveErrors.name: assocReceiveErrors
assocReceiveErrors.description: Frames received with errors from this client.

assocTransmitErrors.name: assocTransmitErrors
assocTransmitErrors.description: Frames transmitted with errors (not acknowledged) for this cleint.

assocCountersEntry.name: assocCountersEntry
assocCountersEntry.description: Entry in the STA association statistics table.

assocAuthenticationCount.name: assocAuthenticationCount
assocAuthenticationCount.description: Number of authentications for this client.

assocDeauthenticationCount.name: assocDeauthenticationCount
assocDeauthenticationCount.description: Number of deauthentications for this client.

assocAssociationCount.name: assocAssociationCount
assocAssociationCount.description: Number of associations for this client.

assocDeassociationCount.name: assocDeassociationCount
assocDeassociationCount.description: Number of deassociations for this client.

assocReassociationCount.name: assocReassociationCount
assocReassociationCount.description: Number of reassociations for this client.

dot11ExtRadioStatsTable.name: dot11ExtRadioStatsTable
dot11ExtRadioStatsTable.description: Table of statistics for the dot11 radio.

dot11ExtRadioType.name: dot11ExtRadioType
dot11ExtRadioType.description: Indicates the type of radio (a/an or b/g/bgn).

dot11ExtRadioInUcastPkts.name: dot11ExtRadioInUcastPkts
dot11ExtRadioInUcastPkts.description: Number of unicast packets from wireless-to-wired network at this radio.

dot11ExtRadioInMcastPkts.name: dot11ExtRadioInMcastPkts
dot11ExtRadioInMcastPkts.description: Number of multicast packets from wireless-to-wired network at this radio.

dot11ExtRadioInBcastPkts.name: dot11ExtRadioInBcastPkts
dot11ExtRadioInBcastPkts.description: Number of broadcast packets from wireless-to-wired network at this radio.

dot11ExtRadioInOctets.name: dot11ExtRadioInOctets
dot11ExtRadioInOctets.description: Total bytes from wireless-to-wired network at this radio.

dot11ExtRadioInErrors.name: dot11ExtRadioInErrors
dot11ExtRadioInErrors.description: Number of error packets from wireless-to-wired network at this radio.

dot11ExtRadioInDiscardsPkts.name: dot11ExtRadioInDiscardsPkts
dot11ExtRadioInDiscardsPkts.description: Number of discarded packets from wireless-to-wired network at this radio.

dot11ExtRadioOutUcastPkts.name: dot11ExtRadioOutUcastPkts
dot11ExtRadioOutUcastPkts.description: Number of unicast packets from wired-to-wireless network at this radio.

dot11ExtRadioOutMcastPkts.name: dot11ExtRadioOutMcastPkts
dot11ExtRadioOutMcastPkts.description: Number of multicast packets from wired-to-wireless network at this radio.

dot11ExtRadioOutBcastPkts.name: dot11ExtRadioOutBcastPkts
dot11ExtRadioOutBcastPkts.description: Number of broadcast from wired-to-wireless network at this radio.

dot11ExtRadioOutOctets.name: dot11ExtRadioOutOctets
dot11ExtRadioOutOctets.description: Total bytes from wired-to-wireless network at this radio.

dot11ExtRadioOutErrors.name: dot11ExtRadioOutErrors
dot11ExtRadioOutErrors.description: Number of error packets from wired-to-wireless network at this radio.

dot11ExtRadioOutDiscardsPkts.name: dot11ExtRadioOutDiscardsPkts
dot11ExtRadioOutDiscardsPkts.description: Number of discarded packets from wired-to-wireless network at this radio.

dot11ExtRadioDeauthCacCount.name: dot11ExtRadioDeauthCacCount
dot11ExtRadioDeauthCacCount.description: Number of deauthentications due to CAC.
